description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Audit assistant &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 x Full Time (37.5hrs) Permanent, 1 x Part-time (30 hrs) Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic, highly motivated computer literate individual to join our busy corporate Clinical Audit Team to support Trust services with quality improvement of patient care and services through clinical audit, evaluation and quality assurance activity across our Trust. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will facilitate Clinical Audit &amp; Effectiveness activity in the Trust, by:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assisting with the development, delivery and promotion of a robust and effective Clinical Audit &amp; Effectiveness Programme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Providing expert knowledge and support to Trust staff with regards to local and national clinical audit and assurance &amp; effectiveness activity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Providing timely and accurate information and reports on audit outcomes to Trust services, to support learning from outcomes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delivering appropriate training to Trust staff&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must demonstrate skills and ability to undertake the above, have proven experience in data review, extraction and interpretation from audit management systems and have excellent written and verbal communication skills with a track record of working efficiently and effectively unsupervised.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please apply early as vacancies may close before the given closing date when sufficient applications are received. Previous applicants need to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you would like to discuss the role, please contact Nakita O’Hanlon on 02087024002 or via email: nakita.ohanlon@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameNakita O’HanlonJob titleClinical Quality Assurance LeadEmail addressnakita.ohanlon@nhs.netTelephone number 02087024002&lt;/p&gt;
